  <h1>Professional LG Dryer Not Spinning Repair Los Angeles County</h1>
  <p>An LG dryer that hums or runs but won't spin the drum almost always comes down to one of three things: a broken drive belt, worn drum rollers or idler pulley, or a failed motor. Our LG Dryer Repair techs check the belt first, since a snapped belt is the most common cause — the motor runs but nothing turns — call (323) 990-7550 for same-day diagnosis.</p>
  <p>When your LG dryer drum stops spinning, clothes pile up fast and laundry day becomes a nightmare. Our technicians diagnose and fix spinning issues in DLGX, DLEX, and DLE series dryers throughout Los Angeles County - call (323) 990-7550 for same-day service.</p>

<h2>Critical Signs Your LG Dryer Needs Professional Spinning Repair</h2>
<p>Across our LG Dryer Repair calls in LA, Orange, and Ventura County, no-spin problems follow a predictable pattern: a broken drive belt is by far the most common cause, followed by worn drum rollers and idler pulley, with motor and drive-coupling failures making up a smaller share.</p>
<p>Nine times out of ten, we get calls from Pasadena and Beverly Hills homeowners who notice these telltale symptoms before their LG dryer completely stops spinning. The drum makes grinding or squealing sounds during cycles, clothes tumble on one side only, or the drum moves freely by hand when the door is open. You might hear the motor running but see no drum movement, or notice the drum spinning intermittently - starting and stopping randomly during cycles.</p>
