<p>The most dangerous sign is burning smells combined with no spinning action. This typically indicates belt friction against seized rollers or motor overheating, which can damage expensive drive components. Our technicians in Torrance and Santa Monica see this escalation weekly when homeowners delay repairs. Other red flags include excessive vibration, the drum feeling loose or wobbly, and error codes like dE2 or PS on newer LG models.</p>
<p>Don't wait for complete failure - partial spinning issues worsen rapidly and often require multiple component replacements instead of single-part fixes.</p>
<h3>When Belt Problems Signal Immediate Service</h3>
<p>Belt-related spinning failures happen suddenly but show warning signs first. You'll hear rhythmic thumping as clothes drop instead of tumbling smoothly, or notice the drum rotating slower than normal. The first thing we check in Glendale and Calabasas service calls is belt tension and alignment - a stretched or misaligned belt creates the characteristic 'clothes not drying evenly' complaint before complete spinning failure.</p>
