About 50% of our spinning-related service calls resolve as minor adjustments or <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-thermal-fuse-replacement/">thermal fuse replacement</a> issues, resulting in service-call-only charges. Returning customers receive 10% labor discounts, and we waive diagnostic fees when repairs proceed. This transparent approach helps Malibu and Newport Beach clients make informed decisions without surprise charges.</p>
<h3>When Replacement Makes Financial Sense</h3>
<p>Replace rather than repair when multiple major components fail simultaneously, typically in dryers over 10 years old. If spinning problems coincide with <a href="/symptoms/lg-dryer-not-heating/">heating issues</a> and control failures, replacement costs approach 60% of new unit prices. Our technicians provide honest assessments and never recommend repairs that don't make economic sense for your specific situation.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>How long does LG dryer spinning repair take?</h3>
<p>Most spinning repairs complete within 45-90 minutes depending on component access and replacement complexity. Belt-only replacements take 30-45 minutes while motor or extensive roller work requires 1-2 hours. Our technicians carry common parts for same-visit completion.</p>
<h3>Can I use my LG dryer if the drum spins slowly?</h3>
<p>Never operate an LG dryer with spinning problems as this damages expensive motor and drive components. Partial spinning creates uneven wear patterns and overheats the motor system. Continued use often escalates simple belt repairs into complex motor replacements.</p>
<h3>Why does my LG dryer drum spin by hand but not during cycles?</h3>
<p>This indicates motor or drive coupling failure rather than belt problems. The motor runs but doesn't engage the drum assembly, typically requiring motor replacement or drive mechanism repair. Professional diagnosis prevents misdiagnosis and incorrect part replacement.</p>
<h3>Do LG dryer spinning repairs come with warranty coverage?</h3>
<p>Yes, all our spinning repairs include 1-year warranty on parts and labor with OEM components only. This covers related component failures and ensures reliable long-term operation. Bureau of Household Goods license #49573 backs our warranty commitments.</p>
<h3>What's included in the LG dryer spinning repair diagnostic?</h3>
<p>Our comprehensive diagnostic tests motor function, belt condition, roller bearings, drive coupling, and electrical connections. We identify all related wear components to prevent callbacks and provide accurate repair estimates. Call (323) 990-7550 for thorough professional diagnosis.</p>
<h3>Why won't my LG dryer drum spin?</h3>
<p>Almost always a broken drive belt, worn drum rollers, or a failed motor. A snapped belt is the most common — you'll hear the motor running but the drum sits still or turns freely by hand. Our techs check the belt and rollers first and confirm the motor with a meter before replacing parts. We're Bureau of Household Goods licensed (#49573).</p>
<h3>How much does it cost to fix an LG dryer that won't spin?</h3>
<p>Most no-spin repairs run $260–350, parts and labor included — a drive belt replacement is on the lower end (around $260–320) and drum roller work runs $280–350. A failed motor is more, $380–480. Our LG Dryer Repair techs confirm the faulty part before quoting, and the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

